  "title": "Safety and Accuracy of Stereoelectroencephalography for Pediatric Patients with Prior Craniotomy",
  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial electroencephalography (iEEG) recordings from stereoelectroencephalography (SEEG) electrode implantations in pediatric patients with a history of prior craniotomy. The data includes electrode coordinates localized in individual native post-operative CT imaging space. All coordinates are recorded in native space with no alignment to other imaging modalities or standardized atlases. This dataset supports clinical and research investigations into the safety and accuracy of SEEG procedures in this patient population.",
